Prose was written by Marshall Bowles. It is inspired by fountain.io.
Read the Getting Started guide to learn how to use proZe.
proZe is an open source set of rules for writing English language prose in plain text.
The main benefit of proZe comes when writing in an a supported editor. You'll get
syntax highlighting of character names as you type, helping you to avoid common
misspellings or accidentally using the wrong character name. Dialogue,
author notes, and commented out portions of the story are visually distinct
to help writers get a quick overview of the structure of their story.
When you're ready, you can convert your proZe files into a document for publishing.
